(144, 1, '2018-03-12 05:51:03', '2018-03-12 05:51:03', '     <h1 class="text-center"> Connecting With Great Companies <br/> With Smart Money. </h1>\r\n		 <ul  class="gallery1">\r\n			 <li><img src="http://bectortechnologies.com/ccedesign/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/img1.jpg"></li>\r\n			 <li><img src="http://bectortechnologies.com/ccedesign/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/img2.jpg"></li>\r\n			 <li><img src="http://bectortechnologies.com/ccedesign/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/img3.jpg"></li>\r\n		 </ul>\r\n		 \r\n		<p> <b>CEE Capital Markets & FinTech Awards strategy includes:  </p>\r\n\r\n		   <p> the Awards Gala – to recognize Top listed and private, PE-backed companies and their top investors, and <p>\r\n		   <p> the Matchmaking/Connect Summit – to help companies connect with institutional investors in a pre-screened, professional environment.</b></p>\r\n\r\n		   <p><b>In 2018, we are expanding our Summit and Awards in <b>two</b> directions:</b> </p>\r\n\r\n		<p><b>a)</b> We will include not only <b>publicly-traded companies but also private companies backed by PE/VCs and promising young companies with high-growth potential.</b> These companies will be from a wide range of sectors, from FinTech to xTech and old-economy companies.</p>\r\n\r\n		<p>b) <b>Matching Investors with Companies. </b>We are connecting Great Companies with Smart Money, focusing on 3 stages in a company''s capital raising life-cycle:<b> Start-Ups; Expansion Stage; and Undiscovered Gems. The aim of the CEE Capital Markets Connect Summit</b> is to connect Great Companies with Smart Institutional Investors.</p>\r\n\r\n		<p>8:00– 9:15<b> Registration and VIP Breakfast</b></p>\r\n\r\n		<p>9:15 – 9:45 <b>Opening KeyNote Address:</b> How CEE''s Companies and Capital Markets are battling to the top of the world''s stage.</p>\r\n\r\n		<p>9:30 – 10:15 <b>VIP Panel: Raising capital in CEE </b>– versus non-<b>CEE</b> options: Capital knows no borders, and companies have a multitude of capital raising options. While CEE markets remain the leading choice, other options include non-public/PE investors from places like Silicon Valley or Israel, and non-traditional public exchanges such as South Africa, Scandinavia, London or the U.S.</p>\r\n\r\n		<p>10:15 – 10:45 <b>Coffee and Networking</b></p>\r\n\r\n		<p>10:45 – 12:30 <b>Break-out Sessions/Matchmaking (49 Companies):</b></p>\r\n\r\n		<p>a) <b>StartUp Pitches: 25</b> brilliant or brash business ideas (for those looking for 100,000 euro to 500,000 euro). Company must be pre-qualified (via website application). Limited to 10 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n		<p>b)<b> “Expansion or Next Stage”: 15</b> revenue-generating companies in next stage of financing (Euro 500,000 -5,000,000). Company must be pre-qualified (via website application). Limited to 15 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n		<p>c) <b>“Undiscovered Gems” – 9</b> Publicly-listed companies set for rapid growth, unanticipated profitability, or exceptional capital gains. Top companies from different sectors present their case. Disruptive business models, unique advantages of CEE-based companies, and overlooked niches in CEE. (Company must be approved by our Investment Partners.) Limited to 25 minutes.</p>\r\n\r\n		<p>12:30 – 14:00 <b>VIP Networking Luncheon</b></p>\r\n\r\n		<p>The Summit concludes at 14:00 and is followed by the evening CEE Capital Markets Connect Awards Gala, beginning at 18:30. </p>\r\n\r\n', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-03-12 05:51:03', '2018-03-12 05:51:03', '', 4, 'http://bectortechnologies.com/ccedesign/2018/03/12/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
